org.gradoop.temporal.model.impl.operators.keyedgrouping

Class TemporalGroupingKeys

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.gradoop.temporal.model.impl.operators.keyedgrouping.TemporalGroupingKeys

  • public final class TemporalGroupingKeys
extends Object
    A factory class for creating instances of commonly used grouping key functions for grouping on temporal attributes.

      • timeStamp

        public static <T extends TemporalElement> KeyFunction<T,Long> timeStamp(TimeDimension interval,
                                                                        TimeDimension.Field intervalField,
                                                                        TemporalField fieldOfTimeStamp)
        Group by a field of a time stamp. The time stamp will be converted to a date with timezone UTC and the field will be extracted from that date. If the field is null, nothing will be extracted and the time stamp will be used as is.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of the elements to group.
        Parameters:
        interval - The time interval to consider.
        intervalField - The field of that interval to consider (i.e. the start- or end-time).
        fieldOfTimeStamp - The field of the date corresponding to that time stamp to consider. (May be null, in that case the time stamp will be used as is.)
        Returns:
        The grouping key function extracting the time stamp or part of it.
        See Also:
        TimeStampKeyFunction
